WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.541
Time to deploy a real app!

00:00:03.541 --> 00:00:06.082
From an empty repo to running

00:00:06.082 --> 00:00:07.775
containers in three moves:

00:00:07.775 --> 00:00:08.199
pick,

00:00:08.199 --> 00:00:08.622
apply,

00:00:08.622 --> 00:00:09.046
run.

00:00:09.891 --> 00:00:12.531
The flow is simple: pick a template, apply

00:00:12.531 --> 00:00:15.091
it to the repo, and run it. The CLI ships

00:00:15.091 --> 00:00:17.891
built-in templates so we never have to write a docker

00:00:17.891 --> 00:00:19.171
-compose from scratch.

00:00:22.561 --> 00:00:23.423
Step one:

00:00:23.423 --> 00:00:25.147
list the available templates.

00:00:25.147 --> 00:00:27.733
Rediacc ships ready-made setups for common

00:00:27.733 --> 00:00:28.164
apps,

00:00:28.164 --> 00:00:30.750
so there is no docker-compose to

00:00:30.750 --> 00:00:32.043
write from scratch.

00:00:33.373 --> 00:00:36.253
The full template catalog. Each one is a tested

00:00:36.253 --> 00:00:38.653
compose plus Rediaccfile pairing.

00:00:42.090 --> 00:00:42.800
Step two:

00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:45.285
drop the app-postgres template into the repo.

00:00:45.285 --> 00:00:47.059
A tested set of files,

00:00:47.059 --> 00:00:48.124
copied straight in.

00:00:53.015 --> 00:00:53.689
Template applied.

00:00:53.689 --> 00:00:56.387
Let us see what actually landed in the

00:00:56.387 --> 00:00:56.724
repo.

00:01:00.005 --> 00:01:02.716
Peek inside the repo and list what

00:01:02.716 --> 00:01:03.103
landed:

00:01:03.103 --> 00:01:05.814
a Rediaccfile holding the start and stop

00:01:05.814 --> 00:01:06.202
hooks,

00:01:06.202 --> 00:01:08.913
and a docker-compose file describing the containers.

00:01:11.913 --> 00:01:12.971
Two files:

00:01:12.971 --> 00:01:15.616
Rediaccfile for the lifecycle hooks,

00:01:15.616 --> 00:01:18.261
and docker-compose.yml for the containers.

00:01:18.767 --> 00:01:20.599
Prefer an editor over cat?

00:01:20.599 --> 00:01:23.165
The same files open in VS Code,

00:01:23.165 --> 00:01:24.630
straight from your browser.

00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:25.730
Here's the Rediaccfile,

00:01:25.730 --> 00:01:28.295
and the compose file next to it.

00:01:28.295 --> 00:01:30.860
We tour this setup properly in a

00:01:30.860 --> 00:01:31.593
later tutorial.

00:01:35.767 --> 00:01:36.570
Step three:

00:01:36.570 --> 00:01:38.177
bring the repo up.

00:01:38.177 --> 00:01:40.988
One command — the CLI mounts the

00:01:40.988 --> 00:01:41.791
encrypted volume,

00:01:41.791 --> 00:01:43.800
starts the isolated Docker daemon,

00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:45.406
and launches the containers.

00:01:48.156 --> 00:01:49.208
Containers running,

00:01:49.208 --> 00:01:50.259
volume mounted,

00:01:50.259 --> 00:01:52.362
isolated Docker daemon up.

00:01:55.686 --> 00:01:57.234
Verify what is running.

00:01:57.234 --> 00:01:59.943
Docker ps here lists only this repo's

00:01:59.943 --> 00:02:00.330
containers.

00:02:00.330 --> 00:02:03.039
Every other repo on this server has

00:02:03.039 --> 00:02:04.200
its own daemon,

00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:06.135
completely invisible from this view.

00:02:07.885 --> 00:02:09.849
Only this repo's containers.

00:02:09.849 --> 00:02:11.814
The isolation is real,

00:02:11.814 --> 00:02:12.796
not configuration.

00:02:13.705 --> 00:02:16.265
And that wraps up your first deploy

00:02:16.745 --> 00:02:19.305
. See you in the next one, where we dig into

00:02:19.305 --> 00:02:21.305
working with the repo itself.
